OL,3,CLife for killer whose partner
OL,4,Cpredicted her own murder
OL,6,FJudge Barry Cotter KC described 55-
OL,7,Fyear-old Spence, who had a string of
OL,8,Fprevious convictions for attacking
OL,9,Fthree other partners, as an "animal".
OL,10,FHe jailed him for life with a minimum
OL,11,Fterm of 24 years.
OL,13,FJudge Cotter told Spence: "You are a
OL,14,Fviolent, manipulative and controlling
OL,15,Fman who has been a danger to women for
OL,16,Fmany years."
OL,18,FDuring Spence's trial, the court heard
OL,19,Fhe had been seeing Ms Varley, who was
OL,20,Fdescribed as a vulnerable drug user,
OL,21,Ffor about six months.
